  "_exec_summary": [
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000050783,
      "SummaryText": "Siltronic Corporation (SCO) operates a facility in Portland, Oregon and manufactures high purity silicon wafers, the basic raw material for the semiconductor and silicon solar industry.  The facility has one administration building, one main process buildings (Fab 2) and several auxiliary support buildings, including water and wastewater treatment facilities.  SCO operates 24 hours per day, 7 days per week, except for occasional shutdowns for preventive maintenance activities, equipment installations, etc.  The manufacture of silicon wafers entails the use of chemicals and the generation of waste, some of which may be listed as toxic or hazardous under U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) regulations.  Currently, SCO uses totes and a tank (each of which is above the threshold quantity) of a CBI acid and a two-tank liquid hydrogen system, with one tank capable of storing more than a threshold quantity (10,000 lbs.) of liquid hydrogen. SCO has extensive equipment inspection, preventive maintenance, on-site emergency response teams, on-site waste treatment facilities, and training programs, spill response and contingency plans.  There have been no accidental releases in the past five years related to the CBI acid or hydrogen."
